In Hinduism, the '''''Ananta Samhita''''' is a recently created scripture, authored by Ananta Vasudeva, a disciple of Srila Bhaktisiddhanta Sarasvati Thakur, founder of the Gaudiya Math. It is supposed to be a [[Pancaratra]] [[Hindu Agamas|agama]], part of the Pancaratra corpus known collectively as the "[[Narada]] Pancaratra" among [[Gaudiya Vaisnava]]s. Please see https://gosai.com/writings/greater-than-the-upanisads-and-the-vedas where Srila Sridhara deva Goswami of Sarasvata Gaudiya Math confirms this book was written by his godbrother Ananta Vasudeva.

