'''Radical 113''' ({{script|Hant|示}} [[Unicode]] U+793A, compound form {{script|Hant|礻}} at U+793B, [[pinyin]] ''{{lang|pny|shì}}'' meaning '''"[[Veneration of the dead|ancestor, veneration]]"''') is number 113 out of  214 [[List of Kangxi radicals|Kangxi radicals]]. It is one of 23 radicals composed of five strokes (the compound form has four strokes). In the [[Kangxi Dictionary]] there are 213 characters (out of 49,030) to be found under this [[Radical (Chinese character)|radical]].

The character {{script|Hant|[[:wikt:示|示]]}} represents an altar or offering table, the top stroke depicting the offered goods. Compare to this the Egyptian ''[[Hotep|ḥtp]]'' hieroglyph <!--<hiero>R4</hiero>--> which has the same motivation of "altar with offering". In the [[seal script]] the table has a {{lang|la|T}} shape.
Semantically, the sign suggests relation to anything connected with animism in [[Chinese folk religion|traditional Chinese religion]], such as [[:wikt:祭|祭]]   "to sacrifice, to practice ancestor veneration", ultimately composed of the sign for meat [[:wikt:肉|肉]] and the sign for a hand [[:wikt:手|手]] above the altar character, as it were iconographically expressing "hand placing  meat on an altar". The sign [[:wikt:祟|祟]] for "spirit" originally referred to misfortune caused by malevolent spirits. 
In [[:wikt:禁|禁]] (''jīn '') "to forbid, restrict, restrain", the [[:wikt:林|林]] (''lín '') above the radical has only phonetic significance ([[rebus writing]]).
Similarly, [[:wikt:神|神]] "spirit" has radical 113 plus [[Radical 102|申]] ''shēn'' as a phonetic marker.
[[:wikt:祖|祖]] "ancestor" on the other hand has radical 113 plus [[:wikt:且|且]], a pictograph of a stand with shelves for offerings to ancestors.

Some signs including the radical have no connection with spirits or animism and are placed in the category purely on formal grounds, such as 票 "ticket" which originally had radical {{script|Hant|[[Radical 86|火]]}} rather than {{script|Hant|示}}.

The compound form {{script|Hant|礻}} always appears in the left half of characters.

